Synthetic re-construction of upstream bug fix
4ce4b31872daa86d01ccab26ad58fbaacd26d978 ("Fix a grave bug in bitIndex").

The buggy `bitIndexInWords` returned the bit's position within the
word it was found in, ignoring how many words had already been
searched. So `bitIndex` would report e.g. `Just 36` for a vector
whose only set bit was at index 100 (= word 1, bit 36). The fix adds
back the word offset (`mulWordSize (n - off)`).

Note: modern `bitIndex` short-circuits to a SIMD C path when the
input is offset 0 *and* word-aligned. The bug only surfaces on the
fallback Haskell path; the property forces non-aligned inputs to
exercise it.

Reverse-applying installs the bug; forward-applying restores the fix.

diff --git a/src/Data/Bit/Immutable.hs b/src/Data/Bit/Immutable.hs
--- a/src/Data/Bit/Immutable.hs
+++ b/src/Data/Bit/Immutable.hs
@@ -644,14 +644,14 @@ bitIndexInWords (Bit True) !off !len !arr = go off
     | n >= off + len = Nothing
     | otherwise = case ffs (indexByteArray arr n) of
       Nothing  -> go (n + 1)
-      r@Just{} -> r
+      Just r  -> Just $ mulWordSize (n - off) + r
 bitIndexInWords (Bit False) !off !len !arr = go off
  where
   go !n
     | n >= off + len = Nothing
     | otherwise = case ffs (complement (indexByteArray arr n)) of
       Nothing -> go (n + 1)
-      r@Just{} -> r
+      Just r  -> Just $ mulWordSize (n - off) + r

 -- | Return the index of the @n@-th bit in the vector
 -- with the specified value, if any.
